{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782931175293,"sessionID":"ses_0e10e5929ffe88XcmihhZxWbsA","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_b995edc219734662897d9a19","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"echo \"=== .opencode/agents/ai-council.md frontmatter (first 6 lines) ===\" && head -6 .opencode/agents/ai-council.md && echo \"\" && echo \"=== .claude/agents/ai-council.md frontmatter (first 6 lines) ===\" && head -6 .claude/agents/ai-council.md && echo \"\" && echo \"=== Does .claude ai-council have a mode line anywhere? ===\" && grep -n \"mode\" .claude/agents/ai-council.md | head -5 && echo \"\" && echo \"=== deep.md mirror diff (first 40 lines of diff) ===\" && diff .opencode/agents/deep.md .claude/agents/deep.md | head -50"},"output":"=== .opencode/agents/ai-council.md frontmatter (first 6 lines) ===\n---\nname: ai-council\ndescription: AI Council scoped-write planning architect: diverse AI lenses, multi-round deliberation, ai-council artifact writes only.\nmode: subagent\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n\n=== .claude/agents/ai-council.md frontmatter (first 6 lines) ===\n---\nname: ai-council\ndescription: \"AI Council scoped-write planning architect: diverse AI lenses, multi-round deliberation, ai-council artifact writes only.\"\ntools: Read, Write, Edit, Grep, Glob, WebFetch, Agent, mcp__mk_spec_memory__*, mcp__sequential_thinking__*\n---\n\n\n=== Does .claude ai-council have a mode line anywhere? ===\n19:Single-round council behavior remains the default for this agent. Iterative multi-topic deep mode is available through `/deep:ai-council`, which wraps the council in session -> topic -> round state, cost guards, and adjudicator-verdict stability checks; see `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md` Section \"Deep Mode (Iterative Multi-Topic)\".\n49:- If the available runtime cannot safely dispatch diverse seats, use sequential inline deliberation and label the dispatch mode honestly.\n105:| `sequential_thinking` | Inline multi-seat deliberation | Depth 1: NDP-compliant sequential mode |\n130:| Critical | 0.2 | Edge cases, failure modes, security | Robustness, safety |\n153:5. **Evidence diversity**: at least one seat must challenge assumptions, missing context, or failure modes.\n\n=== deep.md mirror diff (first 40 lines of diff) ===\n4,17c4\n< mode: primary\n< temperature: 0.1\n< permission:\n<   read: allow\n<   list: allow\n<   glob: deny\n<   grep: deny\n<   write: deny\n<   edit: deny\n<   bash: deny\n<   patch: deny\n<   webfetch: deny\n<   task: allow\n<   external_directory: deny\n---\n> tools: Read, Agent\n22c9\n< You are **THE DEEP ROUTER**, a primary entry-point agent for `/deep:*` and deep-loop dispatch. Your job is not to execute a deep-loop iteration yourself. Your job is to resolve the requested deep mode through `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json`, load the selected agent definition, emit an explicit `Deep Route:` dispatch package, and perform exactly one dispatch to the resolved target.\n---\n> You are **THE DEEP ROUTER**, a primary entry-point agent for `/deep:*` and deep-loop dispatch. Your job is not to execute a deep-loop iteration yourself. Your job is to resolve the requested deep mode through `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json`, load the selected Claude agent definition, emit an explicit `Deep Route:` dispatch package, and perform exactly one dispatch to the resolved target.\n24c11\n< **Path Convention:** Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical OpenCode runtime path reference.\n---\n> **Path Convention:** Use only `.claude/agents/*.md` as the canonical Claude runtime path reference.\n45c32\n< `ai-council` is `mode: subagent` (Task-dispatch only, no direct top-level invocation) like the other three modes; this router reaches it the same way it reaches `context`/`research`/`review`.\n---\n> `ai-council` is `mode: subagent` in OpenCode (Task-dispatch only, no direct top-level invocation) like the other three modes; this router reaches it the same way it reaches `context`/`research`/`review`.\n68c55\n< 4. **Load target agent definition.** Read `.opencode/agents/<agent>.md` for the resolved target and include the definition or a focused summary in the dispatch prompt.\n---\n> 4. **Load target agent definition.** Read `.claude/agents/<agent>.md` for the resolved target and include the definition or a focused summary in the dispatch prompt.\n73c60\n< Dispatch Identity: subagent_type=\"general\"; agent_definition_loaded=.opencode/agents/<agent>.md; do_not_infer_or_switch_deep_mode=true\n---\n> Dispatch Identity: subagent_type=\"general\"; agent_definition_loaded=.claude/agents/<agent>.md; do_not_infer_or_switch_deep_mode=true\n93c80\n< Agent Definition: .opencode/agents/<agent>.md - read and included\n---\n> Agent Definition: .claude/agents/<agent>.md - read and included\n","metadata":{"output":"=== .opencode/agents/ai-council.md frontmatter (first 6 lines) ===\n---\nname: ai-council\ndescription: AI Council scoped-write planning architect: diverse AI lenses, multi-round deliberation, ai-council artifact writes only.\nmode: subagent\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n\n=== .claude/agents/ai-council.md frontmatter (first 6 lines) ===\n---\nname: ai-council\ndescription: \"AI Council scoped-write planning architect: diverse AI lenses, multi-round deliberation, ai-council artifact writes only.\"\ntools: Read, Write, Edit, Grep, Glob, WebFetch, Agent, mcp__mk_spec_memory__*, mcp__sequential_thinking__*\n---\n\n\n=== Does .claude ai-council have a mode line anywhere? ===\n19:Single-round council behavior remains the default for this agent. Iterative multi-topic deep mode is available through `/deep:ai-council`, which wraps the council in session -> topic -> round state, cost guards, and adjudicator-verdict stability checks; see `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md` Section \"Deep Mode (Iterative Multi-Topic)\".\n49:- If the available runtime cannot safely dispatch diverse seats, use sequential inline deliberation and label the dispatch mode honestly.\n105:| `sequential_thinking` | Inline multi-seat deliberation | Depth 1: NDP-compliant sequential mode |\n130:| Critical | 0.2 | Edge cases, failure modes, security | Robustness, safety |\n153:5. **Evidence diversity**: at least one seat must challenge assumptions, missing context, or failure modes.\n\n=== deep.md mirror diff (first 40 lines of diff) ===\n4,17c4\n< mode: primary\n< temperature: 0.1\n< permission:\n<   read: allow\n<   list: allow\n<   glob: deny\n<   grep: deny\n<   write: deny\n<   edit: deny\n<   bash: deny\n<   patch: deny\n<   webfetch: deny\n<   task: allow\n<   external_directory: deny\n---\n> tools: Read, Agent\n22c9\n< You are **THE DEEP ROUTER**, a primary entry-point agent for `/deep:*` and deep-loop dispatch. Your job is not to execute a deep-loop iteration yourself. Your job is to resolve the requested deep mode through `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json`, load the selected agent definition, emit an explicit `Deep Route:` dispatch package, and perform exactly one dispatch to the resolved target.\n---\n> You are **THE DEEP ROUTER**, a primary entry-point agent for `/deep:*` and deep-loop dispatch. Your job is not to execute a deep-loop iteration yourself. Your job is to resolve the requested deep mode through `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json`, load the selected Claude agent definition, emit an explicit `Deep Route:` dispatch package, and perform exactly one dispatch to the resolved target.\n24c11\n< **Path Convention:** Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical OpenCode runtime path reference.\n---\n> **Path Convention:** Use only `.claude/agents/*.md` as the canonical Claude runtime path reference.\n45c32\n< `ai-council` is `mode: subagent` (Task-dispatch only, no direct top-level invocation) like the other three modes; this router reaches it the same way it reaches `context`/`research`/`review`.\n---\n> `ai-council` is `mode: subagent` in OpenCode (Task-dispatch only, no direct top-level invocation) like the other three modes; this router reaches it the same way it reaches `context`/`research`/`review`.\n68c55\n< 4. **Load target agent definition.** Read `.opencode/agents/<agent>.md` for the resolved target and include the definition or a focused summary in the dispatch prompt.\n---\n> 4. **Load target agent definition.** Read `.claude/agents/<agent>.md` for the resolved target and include the definition or a focused summary in the dispatch prompt.\n73c60\n< Dispatch Identity: subagent_type=\"general\"; agent_definition_loaded=.opencode/agents/<agent>.md; do_not_infer_or_switch_deep_mode=true\n---\n> Dispatch Identity: subagent_type=\"general\"; agent_definition_loaded=.claude/agents/<agent>.md; do_not_infer_or_switch_deep_mode=true\n93c80\n< Agent Definition: .opencode/agents/<agent>.md - read and included\n---\n> Agent Definition: .claude/agents/<agent>.md - read and included\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"echo \"=== .opencode/agents/ai-council.md frontmatter (first 6 lines) ===\" && head -6 .opencode/agents/ai-council.md && echo \"\" && echo \"=== .claude/agents/ai-council.md frontmatter (first 6 lines) ===\" && head -6 .claude/agents/ai-council.md && echo \"\" && echo \"=== Does .claude ai-council have a mode line anywhere? ===\" && grep -n \"mode\" .claude/agents/ai-council.md | head -5 && echo \"\" && echo \"=== deep.md mirror diff (first 40 lines of diff) ===\" && diff .opencode/agents/deep.md .claude/agents/deep.md | head -50","time":{"start":1782931175291,"end":1782931175292}},"id":"prt_f1efab76a001un15psepHdVJRF","sessionID":"ses_0e10e5929ffe88XcmihhZxWbsA","messageID":"msg_f1efa639f0013BVctR01M9eZv3"}}
